Walt Disney (December 5, 1901 – December 15, 1966) was an American entrepreneur, film producer, voice actor, and animator best known as the founder of The Walt Disney Company. He is considered one of the most influential people in the history of animation and media.

Early Life and Career

Walt Disney was born on December 5, 1901, in Chicago, Illinois. He grew up in a family of immigrants from Ireland and Scotland. As a child, he was fascinated with drawing and storytelling. He began his career as an animator for a film studio in Kansas City.

In 1923, Disney moved to California to work for a new film studio called Laugh-O-Gram Studios. He soon became dissatisfied with the quality of the animation being produced at Laugh-O-Gram and left to form his own company, Laugh-O-Gram Productions.

Disney's first major success came with his cartoon short film, Steamboat Willie (1928), which featured Mickey Mouse. Mickey quickly became a popular character and was used in many of Disney's future films.

Disney's success led him to found The Walt Disney Company in 1923. Over the next few decades, he produced a series of groundbreaking animated films that captivated audiences around the world, including Snow White and the Seven Dwarfs (1937), Pinocchio (1940), Bambi (1942), Dumbo (1941), Fantasia (1940), Cinderella (1950), Sleeping Beauty (1959), and many others.

Personal Life and Legacy

Throughout his life, Disney remained dedicated to his work and continued to create groundbreaking films until his death in 1966 at age 64. He is considered one of the most influential figures in American media history. His legacy continues to live on through his company, which remains one of the largest entertainment corporations in the world.

Giữa ngôn ngữ: Interpreting between two languages. This can be helpful in situations where communication between individuals or groups may be limited.

Biên dịch: Back translation, also known as inverse translation, is a process of translating a text from one language to another while trying to preserve the original meaning. This can be helpful in situations where a text has been translated incorrectly or needs to be reviewed for accuracy.

Những ví dụ từ của mình:

1. If you're translating from English to Vietnamese, you can use JIT-ed to translate only the parts of the text that are needed. This will help reduce the amount of resources used and save time and money.
2. If you're translating between Vietnamese and another language, you can use back translation to ensure that the meaning is preserved. This will help ensure that important information is not lost in the translation process.
3. If you're translating between Vietnamese and English, you can use just-in-time translation to only translate parts of the text that are needed. This will help reduce the amount of resources used and save time and money.
